The third after three seconds.

477
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:45,240
Seconds will go by, and instruments installed further away will start to record readings.

478
00:36:45,780 --> 00:36:50,700
Since this is a thought experiment, we placed instruments in the Solar system and beyond its limits.

479
00:36:51,420 --> 00:36:57,660
After a year, the instruments located far beyond the limits of the Solar system suddenly start to record readings.

480
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:05,280
The readings will stay unchanged as long as the charge is in our lab and we don't destroy it.

481
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:13,540
Thus, we can easily prove that the energy flow is constant, according to instrument readings.

482
00:37:13,820 --> 00:37:19,340
In real conditions we place instruments much closer to each other, and their number is limited, but this is normal.

483
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:21,880
Enough to prove the principle.

484
00:37:22,460 --> 00:37:25,820
But it'll work if we manage to do this in real conditions.

485
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:31,560
Experimentally, we can easily prove that constant energy flow comes from each charge.

486
00:37:31,860 --> 00:37:34,340
Now the question arises — where does this energy come from?

487
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,840
We can integrate.

488
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:38,460
You know, engineers do this excellently.

489
00:37:39,100 --> 00:37:44,860
They can take instrument readings, integrate the energy density, and calculate the amount of energy at any moment.

490
00:37:45,380 --> 00:37:47,780
It's located in all space, filled with energy.

491
00:37:47,780 --> 00:37:55,720
Of course, energy density falls with distance from the charge — drops as the square for the field and linearly for the potential.

492
00:37:56,900 --> 00:38:01,360
But in any case it won't equal zero across the whole Universe.

493
00:38:02,820 --> 00:38:10,240
Thus, we have huge energy generators — charges, initial charges that extract energy from vacuum.

494
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:13,080
And all electromagnetic energy, all field energy.

495
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:18,680
All fields, all potentials arise thanks to these initial charges.

496
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:20,640
And all this comes from vacuum.

497
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:24,100
Everything we do involves energy from vacuum.

498
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:29,220
We call it electromagnetic field energy, electromagnetic potential energy.

499
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:31,000
And permanent magnets?

500
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:33,360
Permanent magnets are dipoles.

501
00:38:33,640 --> 00:38:35,820
A magnetic charge we call a pole.

502
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:38,320
Magnetic pole.

503
00:38:38,740 --> 00:38:40,480
A permanent magnet is a dipole.

504
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:44,320
The principle of broken symmetry of the dipole also applies to it.

505
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:48,240
A permanent magnet participates in this process constantly.

506
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:57,400
But if the field is absolutely stationary, you can take measurements again and again, and the readings will stay the same at the same point.

507
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,940
You may think it's static.

508
00:39:00,420 --> 00:39:05,840
But it can't be static, since this is a flow, and you can't make a photon stand still in space.

509
00:39:07,720 --> 00:39:10,660
In free space the photon moves at the speed of light.

510
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:15,760
Otherwise we'll have to give up the theory of relativity, including special relativity.

511
00:39:16,100 --> 00:39:17,100
We need to forget about this.

512
00:39:17,100 --> 00:39:18,580
It's not true.

513
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:19,620
It moves.

514
00:39:19,700 --> 00:39:24,700
But the thing is — as Tom Van Flandern emphasized — there are two ways of understanding statics.

515
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:29,060
And he cited a beautiful example with a waterfall.

516
00:39:30,460 --> 00:39:35,640
If the waterfall was truly static — it looks static when it's perfect.

517
00:39:35,820 --> 00:39:41,220
Suppose it's perfect and looks beautiful because at any moment it's the same.

518
00:39:41,220 --> 00:39:45,780
No single element is disturbed, but inside it there's fast movement.

519
00:39:46,120 --> 00:39:48,220
It flows, one part following another.

520
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:50,220
They constantly replace each other.

521
00:39:50,840 --> 00:39:53,060
So such a waterfall isn't completely static.

522
00:39:53,660 --> 00:39:57,400
A fully static one would be a frozen waterfall.

523
00:39:57,400 --> 00:40:03,820
An unfrozen waterfall is what thermodynamics calls a stationary flow.

524
00:40:04,740 --> 00:40:07,320
A system in a non-equilibrium state.

525
00:40:07,600 --> 00:40:13,100
This is when energy constantly comes in and constantly goes out at a constant rate.

526
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:20,160
The state of such a system is defined by the term "constant non-equilibrium state."

527
00:40:20,160 --> 00:40:31,600
In the case of Van Flandern's unfrozen waterfall — which is almost a full analogy of a static field — we see its non-equilibrium stationary state.

528
00:40:31,900 --> 00:40:33,400
Can we prove this?

529
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:34,180
Of course.

530
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:38,580
Thanks to our model we examined, where energy is extracted from vacuum.

531
00:40:38,660 --> 00:40:49,260
In it, a constant flow of energy in a special virtual state passes into the charge that absorbs this flow and transforms it into visible photon energy that it constantly emits at a constant

532
00:40:49,260 --> 00:40:49,840
rate.

533
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:56,860
The charge absorbs energy at a constant rate, transforms and emits it at a constant rate.

534
00:40:56,860 --> 00:41:05,420
And this is a non-equilibrium stationary state in pure form, in which energy is extracted from vacuum and transformed into real energy.

535
00:41:05,420 --> 00:41:07,380
We don't need to transform it ourselves.

536
00:41:07,740 --> 00:41:12,620
I don't need to transform energy from vacuum into real visible energy.

537
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:14,140
Nature already does this.

538
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:16,540
Every charge in the Universe already does this.

539
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:18,940
Every dipole already does this.

540
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:21,340
That is, the EMF just uses this energy.

541
00:41:21,620 --> 00:41:27,420
Everything we do with electrical energy uses what the charges produce by extracting energy from vacuum.

542
00:41:27,420 --> 00:41:33,520
All energy in any electromagnetic circuit is the result of dipole formation in that circuit.

543
00:41:33,880 --> 00:41:35,120
Do you understand what I mean?

544
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:40,620
Charges form dipoles in space, according to the charge model accepted in modern physics.

545
00:41:41,960 --> 00:41:45,380
Everything dipoles do is extracting energy from vacuum.

546
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:48,420
And this has nothing to do with rotating a generator shaft.

547
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:52,760
Why do we rotate the generator shaft?

548
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:57,420
First, let's look at why we need to rotate the shaft at all.

549
00:41:58,780 --> 00:42:00,600
Here we have a wonderful generator.

550
00:42:02,260 --> 00:42:07,940
Since we're smart, the shaft will be rotated by, say, a hydroelectric station turbine, or something of that kind.

551
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:09,700
So we don't have to pay for this.

552
00:42:09,880 --> 00:42:11,820
Only a madman would agree to pay for this.

553
00:42:11,860 --> 00:42:17,440
But otherwise we'd have to burn coal, heat boilers and produce steam so steam turbines could rotate the shaft.

554
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,760
But for this we'd have to pay a lot.

555
00:42:19,760 --> 00:42:26,460
But our generator has a shaft, and we need to constantly rotate it.

556
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:40,240
In electrical engineering we absorbed, you might say, with mother's milk, the concept that the mechanical energy gotten by rotating the shaft is transferred from the outputs to external circuits

557
00:42:43,420 --> 00:42:45,340
and powers all the loads in it.

558
00:42:46,860 --> 00:42:48,600
But this isn't so.

559
00:42:48,700 --> 00:42:50,720
This is completely not so.

560
00:42:51,300 --> 00:42:55,480
First, inside the generator I can do nothing with mechanical energy.

561
00:42:56,100 --> 00:42:58,340
It won't give me even a watt in the transmission line.

562
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:02,860
A transmission line can't transfer mechanical energy.

563
00:43:02,940 --> 00:43:08,080
That is, I need to transform it into a different form inside the generator that would act on charges.

564
00:43:08,180 --> 00:43:10,840
In any case, all energy comes from charges.

565
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:15,440
If I need an energy flow, I separate the charges and get a dipole.

566
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:29,300
If I do this with a rotating field — the concept introduced by Tesla — if I force the rotor inside this generator to rotate, I produce a rotating magnetic field.

567
00:43:29,520 --> 00:43:36,480
Now all the energy that came to the generator as mechanical energy transforms into energy of the rotating magnetic field.

568
00:43:37,480 --> 00:43:38,300
What does it do?

569
00:43:38,300 --> 00:43:41,180
It doesn't go to the transmission line.

570
00:43:41,980 --> 00:43:44,220
It acts on the charges inside the generator.

571
00:43:44,560 --> 00:43:49,500
It forces positive charges to move in one direction, and negative ones in the opposite.

572
00:43:50,820 --> 00:43:55,640
Thus, it gives us dipolarity at the generator outputs.

573
00:43:55,700 --> 00:43:59,540
That is, it's a rough attempt to artificially intensify broken symmetry.

574
00:44:00,140 --> 00:44:00,520
Correct.

575
00:44:00,780 --> 00:44:04,600
Creating broken symmetry of the dipole by means of forming a dipole.

576
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:10,120
We use all the magnetic field energy only to separate charges.

577
00:44:10,420 --> 00:44:19,780
In big schemes this is rather hard to do so the dipole forms, because in front and behind there's a huge amount of electrons that need to be separated to form the dipole.

578
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,700
But suppose you pay for this?

579
00:44:22,120 --> 00:44:27,120
You pay for energy bringing the generator shaft into motion, to separate charges and form the dipole.

580
00:44:27,520 --> 00:44:33,360
Then, if you don't allow anything to happen with the dipole, energy will flow from the generator forever.

581
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:35,540
Why can I claim this?

582
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:36,900
This isn't a perpetual motion machine.

583
00:44:37,280 --> 00:44:40,860
As soon as the dipole appears, energy is constantly extracted from vacuum.

584
00:44:41,240 --> 00:44:42,520
Nature was very kind.

585
00:44:42,620 --> 00:44:44,880
This is already proven by elementary particle physics.

586
00:44:45,100 --> 00:44:47,440
But this knowledge isn't accepted by electrical engineering.

587
00:44:47,520 --> 00:44:49,560
There's not even a concept of "active vacuum."

588
00:44:49,560 --> 00:44:51,060
Where could we extract energy from?

589
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:52,660
It's simply not considered.

590
00:44:52,880 --> 00:44:56,680
In electrical engineering it's considered that it comes from the energy of the generator shaft.

591
00:44:56,700 --> 00:44:57,580
But that's not so.

592
00:44:58,060 --> 00:45:03,200
In any case, as soon as a dipole forms, it starts to interact with the turbulent vacuum.

593
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:06,140
We get a rather big charge in a big generator.

594
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:08,600
And the flow is also big.

595
00:45:09,020 --> 00:45:10,780
A lot of energy comes from here.

596
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:15,820
So, here's an energy flow with thousands of volts.

597
00:45:15,900 --> 00:45:18,620
For example, thousands of volts going along this line.

598
00:45:18,820 --> 00:45:22,520
Transmission lines to power electrical systems.

599
00:45:25,900 --> 00:45:27,620
A strange thing happens.

600
00:45:29,300 --> 00:45:36,940
Two people who discovered the energy flow — came up with the concept of energy flow in space that didn't exist in Maxwell's time...

601
00:45:36,940 --> 00:45:46,860
Maxwell died in 1879, and this concept appeared in the 1880s, and was introduced simultaneously, independently from each other, by Poynting and Heaviside.

602
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:49,180
An interesting thing happens.

603
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:58,600
A small part of the energy flow is located around the conductors — the conductors, on the contrary, have conductivity, like a waveguide, that allows transfer of the energy flow to where needed.

604
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:00,260
That's its function.

605
00:46:02,740 --> 00:46:11,140
The energy around the wire and the various charges of their fields located inside the wire interact with each other, and part of the external energy penetrates into the wires.

606
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:13,780
Very little energy penetrates there.

607
00:46:15,180 --> 00:46:15,920
Quite little.

608
00:46:17,240 --> 00:46:19,960
Very little — possibly up to a ten-trillionth part.

609
00:46:21,140 --> 00:46:28,960
This part that penetrates into the wire was considered by Poynting — he didn't study any other energy except what penetrates into the wire.

610
00:46:29,740 --> 00:46:33,200
He didn't study processes by which energy comes out of the wire.

611
00:46:34,860 --> 00:46:36,540
And a strange thing happens.

612
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:43,760
Heaviside discovered that a lot of energy is lost when all the energy that can penetrate into the wire penetrates in the whole system.

613
00:46:46,720 --> 00:46:49,460
This is much more than what penetrates inside.

614
00:46:49,460 --> 00:46:52,320
But energy is still present outside the wire.

615
00:46:52,760 --> 00:46:56,180
But it won't interact with anything since it's in vortex form.

616
00:46:56,740 --> 00:46:59,900
Dissipation of vortex flow in flat space-time equals zero.

617
00:47:00,320 --> 00:47:01,980
It doesn't interact with anything.

618
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:05,780
Usually most of the space-time we live in is relatively flat.

619
00:47:06,320 --> 00:47:09,660
Thus, we get an amazing thing.

620
00:47:09,780 --> 00:47:20,400
This generator produces and sends along wires a flow of energy trillions of times — maybe even ten trillion times — bigger, most of which is completely unused, than we spend on

621
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:22,840
rotating the generator shaft.

622
00:47:22,920 --> 00:47:30,480
This isn't surprising as soon as we understand that the source of energy is vacuum, not the mechanical energy we use to rotate the shaft.

623
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:38,100
But if you don't understand this — if in your view all this energy is what we apply to the shaft — then for you this is unimaginable.

624
00:47:38,240 --> 00:47:41,680
Because in such case it seems we get energy out of nothing.

625
00:47:42,180 --> 00:47:43,920
There's no source of this additional energy.

626
00:47:43,920 --> 00:47:45,800
Vacuum hasn't yet appeared.

627
00:47:46,100 --> 00:47:46,500
Understand?

628
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:49,640
The concept of active vacuum hasn't reached you yet.

629
00:47:49,840 --> 00:47:50,880
A 19th-century concept.

630
00:47:51,140 --> 00:47:53,160
Where then did they know there was energy?

631
00:47:53,700 --> 00:47:54,580
Heaviside knew this.

632
00:47:55,040 --> 00:48:00,360
Poynting didn't have to think about this since he considered only the dissipating component.

633
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:04,360
He never researched any other flows or components there.

634
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:07,140
He considered all the energy that penetrated the wire.

635
00:48:07,240 --> 00:48:11,220
But he was off by ninety degrees in the flow direction, which Heaviside corrected.

636
00:48:11,220 --> 00:48:14,220
But Heaviside was an amazing person.

637
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:16,180
He had outstanding abilities.

638
00:48:16,700 --> 00:48:20,180
These are his equations that we today call Maxwell's equations.

639
00:48:20,220 --> 00:48:23,100
He simplified them and came up with the notation for them.

640
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:25,160
But he also didn't study at university.

641
00:48:26,760 --> 00:48:29,440
And many mathematicians and other scientists were against him.

642
00:48:31,100 --> 00:48:34,340
He came up with the Heaviside function and many other outstanding things.

643
00:48:35,060 --> 00:48:38,560
At first he was hated, and then his discoveries were accepted and started being used.

644
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:40,880
Heaviside was a loner, almost a hermit.

645
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:44,940
He died a poor starving hermit in a terribly small poor apartment.

646
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:46,500
He starved terribly.

647
00:48:47,480 --> 00:48:54,300
But at the end he got recognition from the Royal Academy and other institutions for his outstanding contribution to science.

648
00:48:55,480 --> 00:49:00,900
Heaviside discovered this additional component, but he didn't dare to talk about it openly.

649
00:49:01,700 --> 00:49:08,260
This soon reached Lorenz, who in the 1890s was the greatest scientist in the field of electricity.

650
00:49:10,340 --> 00:49:12,000
Lorenz understood the works of both.

651
00:49:14,280 --> 00:49:17,000
But even the great Lorenz had limitations.

652
00:49:18,460 --> 00:49:30,380
If he had tried to openly say that yes, each of our generators produces a huge number of times more energy than we spend on it, they'd have tied him up, put him on a train and put him out of

653
00:49:30,380 --> 00:49:30,740
town.

654
00:49:32,380 --> 00:49:37,200
That is, he couldn't do it so as not to lose his reputation and position.

655
00:49:37,640 --> 00:49:39,100
No one would have done so.

656
00:49:40,600 --> 00:49:49,700
If you have a problem you can solve, but the science that would allow this hasn't yet appeared, then you'll be crucified for recognizing it.

657
00:49:51,020 --> 00:49:56,500
And the best way out is to exclude the problem, which is what Lorenz did.

658
00:49:56,900 --> 00:50:05,060
Lorenz taught us to take the energy flow vector as a whole, integrated into a sphere that could be drawn around any point you choose.

659
00:50:06,500 --> 00:50:08,440
This allowed a wonderful thing to be done.

660
00:50:09,140 --> 00:50:10,240
Let's draw a sphere.

661
00:50:10,740 --> 00:50:11,740
This is a round ball.

662
00:50:12,100 --> 00:50:14,260
Some amount of energy comes here.

663
00:50:14,980 --> 00:50:20,340
A small part of it dissipates, and the main part passes further.

664
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:31,400
If we subtract the energy that came out of the sphere from the energy that came into it, we get the dissipated energy — the Poynting component.

665
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:34,620
And every electrical engineer was taught this trick.

666
00:50:34,880 --> 00:50:44,600
But its real goal isn't that this is actually worth doing — but to get rid of the problem they refused to solve for over a hundred years, the solution of which would help

667
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:48,860
get huge amounts of free energy from vacuum.

668
00:50:49,000 --> 00:50:53,540
The question now is whether we can actually use this other component.

669
00:50:54,180 --> 00:50:58,600
By the way, the dissipating Poynting flow now corresponds to all standard concepts.

670
00:50:59,180 --> 00:51:00,900
We power loads.

671
00:51:01,140 --> 00:51:06,900
We collect a large amount of energy and dissipating energy flow along the path of these electrons' movement in the flow.

672
00:51:07,240 --> 00:51:11,800
But the entire current going by the wire in this direction returns back in this direction.

673
00:51:12,880 --> 00:51:23,560
So the voltage along the whole loop from positive output to negative output of the generator is the same, but opposite in sign to the voltage of the current going in the other direction.

674
00:51:24,420 --> 00:51:27,620
First, this is direct EMF pushing current forward.

675
00:51:28,120 --> 00:51:31,420
And second, reverse EMF pushing current in the reverse direction.

676
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:36,400
To force it to go against the voltage, we need to do work.

677
00:51:36,400 --> 00:51:40,840
And when you do this, the charges doing the work will destroy the dipole.

678
00:51:41,160 --> 00:51:43,980
Reverse current equals reverse current at equal voltage.

679
00:51:44,380 --> 00:51:55,320
This confirms the symmetric Lorenz gauge, according to which direct EMF equals reverse EMF, and half of the energy you get from the external circuit you should use for nothing other than

680
00:51:55,320 --> 00:52:00,760
destroying the external source and its ability to extract energy from vacuum and give it to you.

681
00:52:03,460 --> 00:52:06,880
So we destroy the dipole.

682
00:52:07,160 --> 00:52:10,460
Energy comes to the load, and we destroy the dipole.

683
00:52:10,560 --> 00:52:16,520
Half of the energy destroys the dipole, and part of the remaining energy goes out of the circuit as leaks and losses.

684
00:52:16,580 --> 00:52:19,000
That is, less energy comes to the load.

685
00:52:19,120 --> 00:52:23,200
Thus, we spend less on powering the load than on destroying the dipole.

686
00:52:23,560 --> 00:52:29,040
To restore the dipole, we need to do at least the same amount of work to separate the charges.

687
00:52:29,040 --> 00:52:30,940
Apply brute force.

688
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:31,640
Brute force.

689
00:52:31,720 --> 00:52:42,500
That is, here we need to apply the same amount of energy — if your generator has 100% efficiency — to separate charges, restore the dipole and restore the inflow of energy from vacuum.

690
00:52:42,580 --> 00:52:45,260
This amount of energy is more than what's supplied to the load.

691
00:52:45,560 --> 00:52:53,720
Efficiency is defined as the ratio of useful energy reaching the load to the total energy applied at the input of the circuits.

692
00:52:53,720 --> 00:53:02,480
In this case, I'll always have to spend more than reaches the load, so efficiency will be less than one.

693
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:07,080
The ratio of these values will be less than one.

694
00:53:08,280 --> 00:53:17,600
That is, we specifically developed a system — a closed loop that equates direct and reverse EMF currents.

695
00:53:17,600 --> 00:53:27,740
And we leave the generator connected to the circuit so that we can actually destroy the dipole in the generator and the source of energy faster than we feed the load.

696
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:38,380
So to constantly restore dipolarity and get energy from vacuum, we need to rotate the generator shaft, but we'll always apply more energy to the generator than reaches

697
00:53:38,380 --> 00:53:38,920
the load.

698
00:53:39,360 --> 00:53:45,660
This is the absurdity of the modern electric power systems we've developed and built over the last 100 years.

699
00:53:47,180 --> 00:53:48,700
What powers the load?

700
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:52,240
You still have a load and reverse current.

701
00:53:52,660 --> 00:53:53,000
Correct.

702
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:53,860
But not necessarily.

703
00:53:54,540 --> 00:53:59,780
There's no such load by its nature that would say you don't need to use a closed loop.

704
00:54:00,060 --> 00:54:02,040
Tesla switched to single-wire schemes.

705
00:54:02,380 --> 00:54:02,720
Correct.

706
00:54:03,040 --> 00:54:06,700
Supplying a pulse to a capacitor on the other end of the circuit, and then back.

707
00:54:07,240 --> 00:54:13,200
In your vision of the future, it's assumed that we'll develop energy sources that extract energy from vacuum.

708
00:54:14,820 --> 00:54:19,200
How does it fit into the closed schemes of energy use?

709
00:54:19,340 --> 00:54:31,460
The first requirement for getting an electromagnetic system with super-unity efficiency, the first requirement is refusing the closed system that guarantees you need to apply

710
00:54:31,460 --> 00:54:33,620
