Have you found anything new and useful on this topic since the discovery of broken symmetry?

935
01:11:25,980 --> 01:11:29,020
Broken symmetry is now widely used in physics.

936
01:11:29,300 --> 01:11:31,360
Are there any modern works on this topic?

937
01:11:31,420 --> 01:11:32,200
Yes, of course.

938
01:11:32,680 --> 01:11:36,260
One after another, new works appear about symmetry and broken symmetry.

939
01:11:36,420 --> 01:11:37,520
There are millions of works.

940
01:11:39,160 --> 01:11:41,960
Are there new discoveries equal in importance?

941
01:11:42,960 --> 01:11:46,360
New discoveries tend to be understandable only to the initiated.

942
01:11:46,480 --> 01:11:49,380
For example, you've now started asking such questions.

943
01:11:50,020 --> 01:11:52,620
How, in what aspect should we consider reality?

944
01:11:53,700 --> 01:11:56,700
I mean from the standpoint that interests you.

945
01:11:56,760 --> 01:11:57,780
Then yes.

946
01:11:58,380 --> 01:12:00,800
For example, time is now seriously being researched.

947
01:12:01,640 --> 01:12:03,040
What does it represent?

948
01:12:04,300 --> 01:12:06,600
Time can be used as energy.

949
01:12:06,780 --> 01:12:08,680
Time is similar to atomic energy.

950
01:12:09,080 --> 01:12:12,320
It has the same energy density as mass when you convert it.

951
01:12:12,860 --> 01:12:22,480
If you want to develop this aspect, you can take a small period of time and convert it to energy — this small tiny piece of time gives you a huge amount of

952
01:12:22,480 --> 01:12:22,880
energy.

953
01:12:23,040 --> 01:12:24,720
It can be electromagnetic.

954
01:12:25,260 --> 01:12:27,720
One more path we'll eventually go down.

955
01:12:27,720 --> 01:12:37,870
One more conclusion that pushes us — the study of both positive and negative energy, and further straight to Dirac space and Holes before they turn into positrons.

956
01:12:38,400 --> 01:12:44,720
This pushes you to the main question because every energy conservation law is a symmetry.

957
01:12:45,740 --> 01:12:46,300
Understand?

958
01:12:46,860 --> 01:12:58,680
Every time you encounter a violation of symmetry, it's a violation of an energy conservation law — meaning, if you look at the works of Michael Leyton, we now have no structures that

959
01:12:58,680 --> 01:13:00,360
would allow us to reach this level.

960
01:13:00,580 --> 01:13:03,640
But Leyton provided them to us in the late 90s.

961
01:13:03,760 --> 01:13:15,660
If we use object-oriented geometry and the best theoretical methods of grouping, we discover that violation of symmetry at one level doesn't lose all this knowledge, as we always

962
01:13:15,660 --> 01:13:16,240
assumed.

963
01:13:16,240 --> 01:13:20,500
That what happens in nature, knowledge is preserved at some level.

964
01:13:21,080 --> 01:13:24,260
But on a new level in the hierarchy, symmetry is created.

965
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:27,760
The initial charge fully fits into this concept.

966
01:13:28,360 --> 01:13:31,900
You violate symmetry at a lower level in the virtual state.

967
01:13:32,480 --> 01:13:35,420
You automatically create symmetry at the new level.

968
01:13:35,780 --> 01:13:42,600
A new conservation law at the observable state level of electromagnetic field energy, electromagnetic potential energy, and so on.

969
01:13:42,600 --> 01:13:43,940
And this works.

970
01:13:44,120 --> 01:13:51,800
So we developed a new geometry we can use to replace the old 1872 geometry.

971
01:13:52,120 --> 01:14:03,740
If we use Leyton's more modern object-oriented geometry — Michael Leyton — we can understand many things, for example the problem of initial charge and so on.

972
01:14:04,340 --> 01:14:07,680
This is one more fundamental breakthrough we couldn't make before.

973
01:14:07,680 --> 01:14:12,300
Leyton's work is actively applied in robotics and other fields.

974
01:14:12,740 --> 01:14:17,800
His postulates work even when old Euclidean geometry can't solve the problem.

975
01:14:18,360 --> 01:14:21,260
This is successful development, well proven experimentally.

976
01:14:22,420 --> 01:14:27,000
But no one yet applied it to studying initial charge in electrodynamics.

977
01:14:27,300 --> 01:14:29,300
But possibilities for its application are huge.

978
01:14:29,860 --> 01:14:31,520
All I did was point at it.

979
01:14:31,520 --> 01:14:39,360
And youth, postgraduates writing PhD theses, young professors should develop this problem.

980
01:14:39,620 --> 01:14:42,420
This is a whole field not yet studied.

981
01:14:42,800 --> 01:14:45,740
The Department of Energy should pay close attention to it.

982
01:14:46,200 --> 01:14:47,240
But they don't do this.

983
01:14:51,280 --> 01:14:54,980
They don't even know what this is because it isn't what they're working on.

984
01:14:55,060 --> 01:14:56,820
And not what they planned.

985
01:14:57,060 --> 01:14:59,400
A big organization is like a big heavy ship.

986
01:14:59,760 --> 01:15:01,200
You can't turn it instantly.

987
01:15:01,200 --> 01:15:06,420
It goes full steam on its course, and to turn, it needs quite a lot of time.

988
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:12,340
The same is true for all big heavy organizations that change course very slowly.

989
01:15:12,820 --> 01:15:14,020
Sometimes excessively slowly.

990
01:15:14,960 --> 01:15:19,640
It can be changed, but it's always youth that does this.

991
01:15:21,140 --> 01:15:26,360
This is well known, and many scientists say that most scientific discoveries are made by young people.

992
01:15:30,180 --> 01:15:36,340
Einstein was a young Swiss clerk working in the patent office when he came up with relativity, and so on.

993
01:15:38,240 --> 01:15:45,080
What's funniest is that we can change science, even if slowly, only by reaching out to youth and giving them knowledge.

994
01:15:46,340 --> 01:15:48,560
Then they'll come and look up references.

995
01:15:48,560 --> 01:15:57,760
They can make the needed changes, fine-tune everything, accurately model — and they'll give us new technology and new science.

996
01:15:58,100 --> 01:16:00,940
You said time can be used to extract energy.

997
01:16:01,500 --> 01:16:01,700
Yes.

998
01:16:02,440 --> 01:16:03,360
I said it and I say it.

999
01:16:04,900 --> 01:16:09,040
It's not complex when you have special relativity.

1000
01:16:09,440 --> 01:16:15,180
When you use speed, you convert some amount of time into energy — kinetic energy.

1001
01:16:15,180 --> 01:16:22,760
Remember, you need to learn to think within a model that uses only one basic unit — energy.

1002
01:16:23,200 --> 01:16:25,940
Time is energy, a function of energy, like mass.

1003
01:16:26,260 --> 01:16:28,160
Mass as energy doesn't surprise us.

1004
01:16:28,360 --> 01:16:32,780
The atomic bomb appeared, relativity, E equals MC squared.

1005
01:16:33,200 --> 01:16:35,480
Even a humanities student knows this today.

1006
01:16:35,900 --> 01:16:37,180
But at the time it was shocking.

1007
01:16:37,880 --> 01:16:38,640
It was unbelievable.

1008
01:16:38,760 --> 01:16:43,400
People said only 10-12 people in the whole world understood relativity.

1009
01:16:43,400 --> 01:16:46,420
That's how they put it at the time.

1010
01:16:47,300 --> 01:16:49,340
But in subject courses this is normal.

1011
01:16:49,680 --> 01:16:52,700
If young people understand this, knowledge spreads.

1012
01:16:53,120 --> 01:16:57,420
And now millions of people perceive this knowledge as self-evident.

1013
01:16:58,980 --> 01:17:03,860
We're at the stage where we need to make changes of this kind.

1014
01:17:04,880 --> 01:17:07,480
We can get energy from time.

1015
01:17:07,520 --> 01:17:10,520
Take a bit of time, use it and get much energy.

1016
01:17:10,520 --> 01:17:15,840
We can improve many electrical devices and power systems.

1017
01:17:16,260 --> 01:17:22,900
Create a better model, eliminate errors, and then we'll have at our disposal all the energy from vacuum.

1018
01:17:22,980 --> 01:17:24,160
A huge amount of energy.

1019
01:17:24,300 --> 01:17:33,480
We'll have this additional huge component we now ignore — from each generator, accumulator, and all the rest — accessible-for-use Heaviside component.

1020
01:17:34,160 --> 01:17:38,280
This is a rich reserve of energy.

1021
01:17:38,280 --> 01:17:49,580
If we can quickly force country leadership to learn the terms innovative research and innovative science, and perceive them as a basic concept, use them to designate

1022
01:17:49,580 --> 01:17:55,340
funded research programs in this direction, and give young scientists freedom.

1023
01:17:55,440 --> 01:17:59,580
We have many qualified young specialists with excellent training.

1024
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:03,160
Magnificent mathematicians, magnificent theorists, magnificent experimenters.

1025
01:18:03,500 --> 01:18:07,280
We now have more young scientists than ever in the country's history.

1026
01:18:07,280 --> 01:18:09,840
And we use these cadres incorrectly.

1027
01:18:10,260 --> 01:18:11,180
Completely incorrectly.

1028
01:18:11,900 --> 01:18:14,760
We drive everyone under pressure and force them to think stereotypically.

1029
01:18:15,120 --> 01:18:21,040
They're forced to compete for money when studying in postgraduate programs, participating in programs and writing doctoral works.

1030
01:18:21,700 --> 01:18:24,200
We talked about packages of programs funded from above.

1031
01:18:24,680 --> 01:18:26,360
You can't choose your research field.

1032
01:18:26,720 --> 01:18:27,680
It's already chosen for you.

1033
01:18:28,900 --> 01:18:38,300
Electrical engineering or physics department faculties at leading universities don't sit and discuss what they'd want to research.

1034
01:18:39,860 --> 01:18:46,660
They consider what they can get — some funded projects — and what they're ordered to do.

1035
01:18:47,120 --> 01:18:53,460
And then, maybe, something remains for what they'd want to do.

1036
01:18:54,800 --> 01:18:58,180
What's now happening actually suppresses diversity.
